To find the inverse of a 2x2 matrix, we can use the following formula:

$$
\begin{pmatrix}
a & b \\
c & d
\end{pmatrix}^{-1}
=
\frac{1}{ad - bc}
\begin{pmatrix}
d & -b \\
-c & a
\end{pmatrix}
$$

In this case, our matrix is:

$$
\begin{pmatrix}
5 & 1 \\
-2 & 3
\end{pmatrix}
$$

So, a = 5, b = 1, c = -2, and d = 3. First, we need to find the determinant (ad - bc):

$$
\text{Determinant} = (5)(3) - (1)(-2) = 15 + 2 = 17
$$

Now we can find the inverse using the formula:

$$
\frac{1}{17}
\begin{pmatrix}
3 & -1 \\
2 & 5
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
\frac{3}{17} & -\frac{1}{17} \\
\frac{2}{17} & \frac{5}{17}
\end{pmatrix}
$$

So, the inverse of the given matrix is:

$$
\begin{pmatrix}
\frac{3}{17} & -\frac{1}{17} \\
\frac{2}{17} & \frac{5}{17}
\end{pmatrix}
$$
